pull_request.title: find entry first, then createObject to avoid too many unreference entry alloced
pull_request.body:
try to fix bug:#29929
There are max of 4 unsecure sessions default( defined by CHIP_CONFIG_UNAUTHENTICATED_CONNECTION_POOL_SIZE), if the CASE sigma1 was received more than 4 times. The mEntries in UnauthenticatedSessionTable will never release object, as in AllocEntry of UnauthenticatedSessionTable , it will CreateObject first, but it is less memory consumption to call FindLeastRecentUsedEntry first.

issue.title: [CERT-TEST-FAILURE] - TC-SWTCH-2.2 - Test failed
issue.body:
### Feature Area

Other

### Test Case

TC-SWTCH-2.2

### Reproduction steps

In Switch clusters all the Events are depending on the Feature support
1. SwitchLatched event is supports when LatchingSwitch feature is enable.
2. All other Below mentioned events will supports when MomentarySwitch feature is enabled. 

- InitialPress
- LongPress
- ShortRelease
- LongRelease
- MultiPressOngoing
- MultiPressComplete

As per the spec, conformance of LatchingSwitch and MomentarySwitch fetures is O.a means exactly one of the "a" elements SHALL be supported.

Here
If LatchingSwitch feature is enabled, all remaining feture bit will be set to 0.

If MomentarySwitch feature is enabled, Only LatchingSwitch feature bit wiil be set to 0.

Now in current SDK getting feature map value as 1. Means bit 0 is set to 1, LatchingSwitch feature is enabled and it dependent event should support. All the remaining feature bit is set to 0 then these feature dependent events should not support, But currently in SDK it is supporting all the events.  

### Bug prevalence

Whenever I do

### GitHub hash of the SDK that was being used

f4735790763692462c0803be35c808d52741ffb4

### Platform

raspi

### Anything else?

**Specification Reference:**
https://github.com/CHIP-Specifications/connectedhomeip-spec/blob/master/src/app_clusters/Switch.adoc#4-features

**Reference Log:**
[TC-SWTCH-2.2(CNTRL).txt](https://github.com/project-chip/connectedhomeip/files/13188015/TC-SWTCH-2.2.CNTRL.txt)
[TC-SWTCH-2.2(DUT2).txt](https://github.com/project-chip/connectedhomeip/files/13188016/TC-SWTCH-2.2.DUT2.txt)
[TC-SWTCH-2.2(DUT).txt](https://github.com/project-chip/connectedhomeip/files/13188018/TC-SWTCH-2.2.DUT.txt)

issue.title: [CERT-TEST-FAILURE] - TC-FAN - Test failed
issue.body:
### Feature Area

Other

### Test Case

TC-FAN-2.3 and 3.3

### Reproduction steps

1. Bring up the DUT with `all-clusters-app`.
2. Pair the DUT using chip-tool through "onnetwork" transport.
3. Run the command `./chip-tool fancontrol read rock-support 1 1`

**Expected Outcome:**

> [1689757789.384816][23225:23227] CHIP:TOO: Endpoint: 1 Cluster: 0x0000_0202 Attribute 0x0000_0007 DataVersion: 1958137194
> [1689757789.384890][23225:23227] CHIP:TOO:   RockSupport: 7

**Actual Outcome:**

> [1689757789.384816][23225:23227] CHIP:TOO: Endpoint: 1 Cluster: 0x0000_0202 Attribute 0x0000_0007 DataVersion: 1958137194
> [1689757789.384890][23225:23227] CHIP:TOO:   RockSupport: 3

4. Run the command `./chip-tool fancontrol write rock-setting 4 1 1`

**Expected Outcome:**

> [1685104690.737980][30753:30755] CHIP:DMG:                         StatusIB =
> [1685104690.738051][30753:30755] CHIP:DMG:                         {
> [1685104690.738122][30753:30755] CHIP:DMG:                                 status = 0x00 (SUCCESS),
> [1685104690.738199][30753:30755] CHIP:DMG:                         },

**Actual Outcome:**

> [1698391538.200153][42308:42310] CHIP:DMG: 			StatusIB =
> [1698391538.200190][42308:42310] CHIP:DMG: 			{
> [1698391538.200224][42308:42310] CHIP:DMG: 				status = 0x87 (CONSTRAINT_ERROR),
> [1698391538.200261][42308:42310] CHIP:DMG: 			},



### Bug prevalence

Whenever I do this 

### GitHub hash of the SDK that was being used

f4735790763692462c0803be35c808d52741ffb4

### Platform

raspi

### Anything else?

- As per the SPEC, the `RockSupport and RockSetting` attributes depend on the ROCKING feature which has already been implemented in the all-clusters-app. 
- Also, the data type of the RockSupport and RockSetting attributes should be as per RockBitmap, this RockBitmap has three mandatory bits. However, the bit 2 `RockRound` is not currently implemented in the sample app. 
- Therefore, it is necessary to implement bit 2 (RockRound) in the current sample app.

**Specification References:**

![Screenshot from 2023-10-27 13-17-39](https://github.com/project-chip/connectedhomeip/assets/133193761/03373876-6267-4224-b02d-84242a109dc3)

![Screenshot from 2023-10-27 13-18-21](https://github.com/project-chip/connectedhomeip/assets/133193761/e9d823f3-a187-4029-ae80-96361b203b24)

issue.title: [Infineon]Update button init sequence before wifi commissioning
issue.body:
Fixes https://github.com/project-chip/connectedhomeip/issues/29611

- Support button init before wifi commissioning sequence in-order to do factory reset during error scenarios.
- Add chip lock/unlock before calling starttimer as it was causing chipDie during wifi connect retry sequences (if wifi password is wrong)
